</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
    <label><input type="radio" name="q2"> Done</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="q2"> Revisit</label>
  </div>
  <div class="task-title">2. Assign Static IP</div>
  Set the following on <b>clone-client</b> if your network is different please use your own subnet but set host 130:  
  <ul>
    <li>IP: 192.168.100.130</li>
    <li>Netmask: 255.255.255.0</li>
    <li>Gateway: 192.168.1.1</li>
    <li>NameServer: 192.168.1.1</li>
    <li>Hostname: servera.example.com</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
    <label><input type="radio" name="q3"> Done</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="q3"> Revisit</label>
  </div>
   <div class="task-title">3. Container Management I</div>
   Login the registry “registry.redhat.io” using your credentials.</br>
   Create a container image using the given link.
   <ul>
	   <b>a)</b> Login as the <b>frank</b> user, clone the repository from https://github.com/saim-ali-hub/batch-2025-client.git, and build a container image using the provided <b>Containerfile25</b>. Name the resulting image <b>webimage25</b>.</br>
	   <b>b)</b> Login as the <b>linda</b> user, build a container image using the provided <b>Containerfile</b>. Name the resulting image <b>webimage</b>.
   </ul>
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
    <label><input type="radio" name="q4"> Done</label>
    <label><input type="radio" name="q4"> Revisit</label>
  </div>
  <div class="task-title">4. Container Management II</div>
  Create a rootless container using the following conditions.
  <ul>
	  <b>a)</b> As local user <b>frank</b>, create a container called <b>container25</b> from image <b>webimage25</b>. Mount <b>/opt/mydata</b> inside container on <b>/opt/newdata</b> and mount <b>/opt/web</b> on <b>/var/www/html</b>. The container port <b>8080</b> should be mapped with host port <b>9092</b>. Also, manage this container as systemd service and it should be boot persistent. Further create a file named <b>my_file1.pdf</b> in <b>/opt/process</b> that should available in <b>/mnt/new</b> inside container.</br>
          <b>b)</b> As local user <b>linda</b>, create a container called <b>myweb</b> from image <b>webimage</b>. mount <b>/opt/process</b> inside container on <b>/mnt/new</b> and mount <b>/opt/action</b> on <b>/mnt/old</b>. The container port 8080 should be mapped with host port <b>8085</b>. Also, manage this container as systemd service and it should be boot persistent.
</ul>
</div>

<div class="task">
  <div class="options">
